Saddle up to find out what makes horses one of the most trusted companions you could ever have!

Spot horse-drawn carriages (trolleys) on Main Street U.S.A., at Magic Kingdom park. To interact with majestic looking horses, take a smooth sleigh ride or a scenic jaunt along a trail at Disney’s Fort Wilderness Resort and Campground. You can also see a variety of breeds including Quarter Horse, Percheron, Paint, Gypsy Vanner, Clydesdale, Belgian, Appaloosa, Arabian and Shetland ponies, at Tri-Circle-D Ranch.

name: Innoventions
description:

The SpectacuLAB Presented by Murata 

Join the SpectacuLAB scientists and their tech-savvy intern for a funny and fascinating show that demonstrates basic principles of science.


Colortopia

In Colortopia Presented by Glidden, you’ll experience the wonderful world of color. Explore 3 interactive zones—the Color Lab, Color Our World Studio and Power of Color Theater—for a fun, informative take on the many ways color affects our lives. From creating custom hues with a digital paint palette to understanding how different shades can impact moods, you’ll learn how every color tells a story.

name: Star Wars™: Secrets of the Empire by ILMxLAB and The VOID
description:
The galaxy needs you! Under disguise in teams of 4, recover Imperial intelligence vital to the budding Rebellion’s survival during a cutting-edge hyper-reality experience.

Be transported with family and friends to a galaxy far, far away on a multi-sensory, untethered hyper-reality adventure.

Disney Springs introduces Star Wars™: Secrets of the Empire, a transformative story by ILMxLAB and The VOID that merges our world with virtual reality.

Surrounded by cutting-edge 3D imagery and sound, Guests can move around freely while virtually interacting with popular Star Wars characters—as well as each other—in a multi-sensory environment that combines groundbreaking technology, virtual reality and the magic of illusion.

Please note: all Guests must accept The VOID’s Liability Waiver, Terms & Conditions, and Privacy Policy before entering The VOID. Guests under 16 years of age must have a parent or guardian present at The VOID location to sign the documents in person.

Purchase Your Tickets Today
